com.raweng.built

Class BuiltUser

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.raweng.built.BuiltUser

  • public class BuiltUser
extends java.lang.Object
    This class allows registering user for an application and other features such as logging in and logging out.
    After the log in, the getAuthToken() will be given in response. This getAuthToken() is to be supplied for subsequent requests if the the request is to be identified as being from that user.
    Author:
    raw engineering, Inc

      • register

        public BuiltUser register(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> userInfo,
                 com.raweng.built.BuiltResultCallBack callback)
        Request to register user.
        Parameters:
        userInfo - HashMap object containing user info . UserInfo object contains following keys :
        email: required,
        password:required,
        password_confirmation:required,
        username:optional,
        first_name:optional,
        last_name:optional,
        anydata:anyvalue
        callback - BuiltResultCallBack object to notify the application when the request has completed.
        Returns:
        BuiltUser object, so you can chain this call.

        Note:

      • You can access application user data by accessing getAuthToken(), getUserUid(), getFirstName(), getLastName(), getUserName(), getEmailId()

      • updateUserInfo

        public BuiltUser updateUserInfo(java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> userInfo,
                       com.raweng.built.BuiltResultCallBack callback)
        To Update logged in user info.
        Parameters:
        userInfo - HashMap object containing user info . UserInfo object contains following keys :
      • first_name
      • last_name
      • Tibbr
      • Google
      • password
      • old_password
      • password_confirmation
      • customField

      • first_name: Add this key to edit first name.
      • last_name: Add this key to modify last name.
      • old_password: Add this key to change password, This will be your current password.
        To update password, you have to add "password_confirmation" and "password" key too.
      • password : Add this key to change password, This will be your current password.
        To update password, you have to add "old_password" and "password_confirmation" key too.
      • password_confirmation: Add this key to change password, This will be your new password.
        To update password, you have to add "old_password" and "password" key too.
      • customField :
        • Other field Uid than above.
        callback - BuiltResultCallBack object to notify the application when the request has completed.
        Returns:
        BuiltUser object, so you can chain this call.

        Note:

      • You can access application user data by accessing getAuthToken(), getUserUid(), getFirstName(), getLastName(), getUserName(), getEmailId()

        • Usage 

        
 HashMap userInfoHashMap = new HashMap();
 userInfoHashMap.put("first_name", "FirstName"); // to change first name.
 userInfoHashMap.put("last_name", "LastName"); // to change last name.
 userInfoHashMap.put("Google", "accessToken"); // to update 2.0 oAuth token.
 

 HashMap tibbrInfoHashMap = new HashMap(); // to update tibbr access token.
 tibbrInfoHashMap.put("accessToken", "tibbrAccessToken"); // tibbr access token.
 tibbrInfoHashMap.put("host", "tibbrHost"); // tibbr host. tibbr host name must be supply in "https://customhost.tibbr.com" format.
 userInfoHashMap.put("Tibbr", tibbrInfoHashMap);
 

        userInfoHashMap.put("old_password", "currentPassword"); // to change password.
        userInfoHashMap.put("password", "newPassword");
        userInfoHashMap.put("password_confirmation", "newPassword");
 
 
 builtUserObject.updateUserInfo(userInfoHashMap, new BuiltResultCallBack() {......}

      • fetchUserUidForEmail

        public void fetchUserUidForEmail(java.lang.String emailId,
                        com.raweng.built.BuiltUserResultCallback callback)
        To retrieve user uid using specified email id.
        Parameters:
        emailId - email id.
        callback - BuiltUserResultCallback object to notify the application when the request has completed.

        Note :

      • This call will allow you to retrieve the uid for an user, whether or not the user exists. A means for identifying the user needs to be provided. This comes in handy, for example, when you need to apply ACL for an user that may not exist in the system at the moment.

      • saveSession

        public void saveSession()
                 throws java.lang.Exception
        Saves current logged-in builtUser on disk.

        Usage: 

         final BuiltUser user = new BuiltUser();
 user.login("abc@xyz.com", "password",new BuiltResultCallBack() {
         
         @Override
         public void onSuccess() {
                        try {
                                user.saveSession();
                        } catch(Exception error) {
                                Log.i("SaveSession", "--Error while saving session|" + error);
                        }
          }

         @Override
         public void onError(BuiltError error) {}

         @Override
         public void onAlways() {}
  });

        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • getGoogleAccessToken

        public java.lang.String getGoogleAccessToken()
        Google oauth 2.0 access token from google used to log a user into your application. Access token is short lived, it will get expired in sometime. Returns google access token in BuiltUILoginController success override method.
        Returns:
        google oauth 2.0 access token.
        Example

            public void loginSuccess(BuiltUser user) {

                 String googleAccessToken = user.getGoogleAccessToken();


                }
